FBIS4-64174 "drsov104_t_94006" FBIS-SOV-94-104 Daily Report 30 May 1994 BALTIC STATES Estonia Declaration To Begin Free Trade Talks With Slovenia Signed Declaration To Begin Free Trade Talks With Slovenia Signed WS3105085694 Tallinn ETA in English 0701 GMT 30 May 94 WS3105085694 Tallinn ETA English BFN [From 30 May RAHVA HAAL, p.1; "News Bulletin" No. 106/94 ] [Text] Estonian Prime Minister Mart Laar and Slovenian Prime Minister Janez Drnovshek signed a declaration to begin free trade negotiations. Estonia has already started such talks with Poland, Hungary and Czech Republic. According to Laar Slovenia may become a "gate to former Yugoslavia, also to Italy". Laar remarked on the similarity of security problems in Estonia and Slovenia and mentions the possibility of defence cooperation. Estonia has appointed Sven Jurgenson for its charge d'affaires in Slovenia. Slovenian Prime Minister had a positive attitude to Estonia's suggestion to enact visa-free travel.
